The '''Chuck Bednarik Award''' is presented annually to the [[defence (sport)|defensive]] player of the year in [[college football]] as judged by the [[Maxwell Football Club]] to be the best in the [[National Collegiate Athletic Association|United States]]. The award is named for [[Chuck Bednarik]], a former college and professional [[American football]] player. Voters for the Maxwell College Awards are NCAA head college football coaches, members of the Maxwell Football Club, and sportswriters and sportscasters from across the country. The Maxwell Club is located in [[Philadelphia, Pennsylvania]] and the presentations are held in [[Atlantic City, New Jersey]]. Club members are given voting privileges for the award.

